The paper discusses the use of connectionist AI systems and weighted graphs for planning, which are common topics in the cs.AI and cs.NE sub-categories. The paper also introduces a new discrete planning algorithm and discusses its application in communication, which falls under the cs.DS and cs.IT sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of electrical networks for connectionist AI, which is relevant to the cs.SY sub-category.
